From 11835e4057029d1296b4029c372e9a9e8a5b2b7b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Micheal Waltz <micheal@ecliptik.com>
Date: Sun, 26 Apr 2026 17:13:42 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] [DOSKUTSU] dos: SDL_HINT_DOS_PREFER_LFB to flip the
 LFB-vs-banked decision (lever 1 perf)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Phase 9 lever 1. Adds a new public hint SDL_HINT_DOS_PREFER_LFB that, when
set to "1", flips the LFB-vs-banked decision in DOSVESA_SetDisplayMode so
LFB wins over banked when the BIOS reports both available.

Default behaviour stays exactly as before: prefer banked when usable,
which is correct on the cards SDL3-DOS PR #15377 was developed against.

The flip is required for ATI Mach64 / M64VBE on the g2k Pentium OverDrive
reference machine where banked-mode VESA writes through the 0xA0000
window are bandwidth-bound at ~500 KB/s effective and LFB through
DPMI-mapped VRAM is 5-10× faster (docs/PHASE8-FINDINGS.md).

Precedence
----------

When BOTH SDL_HINT_DOS_PREFER_LFB and SDL_HINT_DOS_ALLOW_DIRECT_FRAMEBUFFER
are set, PREFER_LFB wins at the use_lfb decision. The older hint is then
treated as a fast-path opt-in only — for our DOSKUTSU build that's
exactly right: ALLOW_DIRECT_FRAMEBUFFER stays "1" because patch 0032's
side-effect is what makes the fb_state init populate correctly on the
banked path; PREFER_LFB="1" overrides the policy choice on top.

Patch 0011 will follow up with the lazy-fb_state-init fix that makes
LFB actually engage in fb_state across mode-change boundaries — Phase 8
attempt at this same hint failed because the surface-recreation
lifecycle was missing the fb_state re-population step. The hint is
no-op without 0011's fix; ship them together.

Why DOS needs this
------------------

DOS-only hint to flip a DOS-backend-only policy. No effect on non-DOS
builds.

Local-only patch per workspace policy (memory note "SDL upstream —
local patches only"): never PR'd upstream, sidestepping
vendor/SDL/CLAUDE.md's no-AI-PRs restriction.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 include/SDL3/SDL_hints.h     | 35 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c | 35 ++++++++++++++++++++++-------------
 2 files changed, 57 insertions(+), 13 deletions(-)

diff --git a/include/SDL3/SDL_hints.h b/include/SDL3/SDL_hints.h
index da0481360..486a0d3ab 100644
--- a/include/SDL3/SDL_hints.h
+++ b/include/SDL3/SDL_hints.h
@@ -741,6 +741,41 @@ extern "C" {
  */
 #define SDL_HINT_DOS_ALLOW_DIRECT_FRAMEBUFFER "SDL_DOS_ALLOW_DIRECT_FRAMEBUFFER"
 
+/**
+ * A variable that requests Linear Framebuffer (LFB) over the banked VGA
+ * window when both are available on a DOS VBE mode.
+ *
+ * Default behaviour at the LFB-vs-banked decision in
+ * src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c is: prefer banked when banked is usable,
+ * even if the BIOS reports LFB available. This is correct on cards
+ * where the banked window is faster than nearptr writes through DPMI-
+ * mapped LFB (some NVIDIA cards in older BIOSes; the SDL3-DOS PR
+ * #15377 author's empirical finding).
+ *
+ * On other cards (notably ATI Mach64 with M64VBE on the g2k Pentium
+ * OverDrive reference machine), banked-mode VESA writes are bandwidth-
+ * bound at ~500 KB/s effective, while LFB through DPMI-mapped VRAM is
+ * 5-10× faster. Setting this hint to "1" flips the policy so LFB wins
+ * the decision when available.
+ *
+ * The variable can be set to the following values:
+ *
+ * - "0": Use the existing logic (prefer banked when usable). (default)
+ * - "1": Prefer LFB when available. Banked is fallback.
+ *
+ * When BOTH this hint and SDL_HINT_DOS_ALLOW_DIRECT_FRAMEBUFFER are set,
+ * SDL_HINT_DOS_PREFER_LFB takes precedence at the use_lfb decision —
+ * the older hint is interpreted as "fast-path opt-in" only.
+ *
+ * This hint must be set before the first call to SDL_GetWindowSurface()
+ * (or any function that triggers VBE mode-set, including SDL_CreateWindow
+ * with the SDL_WINDOW_FULLSCREEN flag).
+ *
+ * Added by patches/SDL/0010 (DOSKUTSU local patch, never upstreamed).
+ * See docs/PHASE9-15FPS-PLAN.md §3 Lever 1.
+ */
+#define SDL_HINT_DOS_PREFER_LFB "SDL_DOS_PREFER_LFB"
+
 /**
  * A variable that caps VESA mode enumeration on DOS to a maximum bits-per-
  * pixel.
diff --git a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c
index ce25712d1..732061960 100644
--- a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c
+++ b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosmodes.c
@@ -682,22 +682,31 @@ bool DOSVESA_SetDisplayMode(SDL_VideoDevice *device, SDL_VideoDisplay *sdl_displ
 
     // When the direct-FB hint is active, prefer banked mode. This needs
     // to be set explicitly for some cards (Intel 740).
+    //
+    // DOSKUTSU patch 0010: SDL_HINT_DOS_PREFER_LFB inverts that policy —
+    // when set, LFB wins over banked even when banked is usable. Required
+    // for ATI Mach64 / M64VBE on the g2k Pentium OverDrive reference
+    // hardware where banked-mode VESA writes are bandwidth-bound and LFB
+    // is 5-10× faster (docs/PHASE8-FINDINGS.md). PREFER_LFB takes
+    // precedence over ALLOW_DIRECT_FRAMEBUFFER when both are set.
     const bool is_banked_usable = modedata->win_a_segment &&
                                   modedata->win_size > 0 &&
                                   (modedata->win_a_attributes & VBE_WINATTR_USABLE) == VBE_WINATTR_USABLE;
     const bool hint_allow_direct = SDL_GetHintBoolean(SDL_HINT_DOS_ALLOW_DIRECT_FRAMEBUFFER, false);
+    const bool hint_prefer_lfb = SDL_GetHintBoolean(SDL_HINT_DOS_PREFER_LFB, false);
     const bool use_lfb = modedata->has_lfb &&
-                         (!is_banked_usable || !hint_allow_direct);
-
-    // DOSKUTSU diagnostic (patch 0009): make the LFB-vs-banked decision
-    // explicit so we can SEE *why* each mode-set chose what it chose.
-    // hint_allow_direct=1 forces banked even when LFB is available — this
-    // is the policy lever patch 0010 will invert. lfb_available comes
-    // straight from BIOS-reported mode attrs.
-    DOSKUTSU_MODES_LOG("LFB-decision #%d: hint_allow_direct=%d lfb_available=%d "
-                       "is_banked_usable=%d -> use_lfb=%d",
-                       ms_calls, (int)hint_allow_direct, (int)modedata->has_lfb,
-                       (int)is_banked_usable, (int)use_lfb);
+                         (hint_prefer_lfb ||
+                          !is_banked_usable ||
+                          !hint_allow_direct);
+
+    // DOSKUTSU diagnostic (patch 0009 + 0010): make the LFB-vs-banked
+    // decision explicit so we can SEE *why* each mode-set chose what it
+    // chose. hint_allow_direct=1 historically forced banked; patch 0010
+    // adds hint_prefer_lfb which now wins over hint_allow_direct.
+    DOSKUTSU_MODES_LOG("LFB-decision #%d: hint_allow_direct=%d hint_prefer_lfb=%d "
+                       "lfb_available=%d is_banked_usable=%d -> use_lfb=%d",
+                       ms_calls, (int)hint_allow_direct, (int)hint_prefer_lfb,
+                       (int)modedata->has_lfb, (int)is_banked_usable, (int)use_lfb);
 
     regs.x.ax = 0x4F02;
     regs.x.bx = modedata->mode_id | (use_lfb ? VBE_SETMODE_LFB : 0);
@@ -718,7 +727,7 @@ bool DOSVESA_SetDisplayMode(SDL_VideoDevice *device, SDL_VideoDisplay *sdl_displ
     DOSKUTSU_MODES_LOG("DOSVESA-MODESET: id=0x%04X %dx%d %dbpp pitch=%d attr=0x%04X memmodel=%d "
                        "has_lfb=%d use_lfb=%d banked=%d "
                        "lfb_addr=0x%08lX win_seg=0x%04X win_size=%uKB win_gran=%uKB win_attr=0x%02X "
-                       "win_func=0x%08lX hint_direct_fb=%d",
+                       "win_func=0x%08lX hint_direct_fb=%d hint_prefer_lfb=%d",
                        modedata->mode_id, modedata->w, modedata->h, modedata->bpp, modedata->pitch,
                        modedata->attributes, modedata->memory_model,
                        (int)modedata->has_lfb, (int)use_lfb, (int)data->banked_mode,
@@ -726,7 +735,7 @@ bool DOSVESA_SetDisplayMode(SDL_VideoDevice *device, SDL_VideoDisplay *sdl_displ
                        modedata->win_a_segment, (unsigned)modedata->win_size,
                        (unsigned)modedata->win_granularity, modedata->win_a_attributes,
                        (unsigned long)modedata->win_func_ptr,
-                       (int)hint_allow_direct);
+                       (int)hint_allow_direct, (int)hint_prefer_lfb);
 
     if (use_lfb) {
         data->mapping.address = modedata->physical_base_addr;
-- 
2.47.3

